<br>
She would have been riding her broom except it was busy enough carrying a cauldron she had filled with dark chocolate after a bit of transfiguration.  The tapping of her footsteps noise grew closer and closer to the large solid door that had edged its way closed as she had come towards it.  Almost there Amber traded her trot into a full run the smile fading from her face in concentration.  Swinging up onto broom she gave the door a good kick with one foot to open it as she let the other slide down the broom until it rested right before the handle of the cauldron.  As she swept into the room she kicked back so the cauldron slid off to land on the floor as she took her seat on her broom.  Circling the room once she ducked down to grab a piece of chocolate from her cauldron and then floated on her broom so her head was the same level as the 7th year's were.  The little actress's eyes were even and she watched the room as if she saw it all daily and it was nothing new.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hope you won't mind another one along for the ride,&quot; she said calmly shaking Kerri's hand, &quot;You didn't think I would miss out on this did you?&quot; <p><font color="Cornflowerblue">
